WEBVTT

00:07.736 --> 00:08.903
<i>And that's your biggest worry?</i>

00:08.903 --> 00:11.281
<i>Yes, any kind of virus, but most probably
something similar to influenza.</i>

00:11.281 --> 00:12.615
1968

00:12.615 --> 00:13.700
<i>Because of air travel.</i>

00:13.700 --> 00:14.743
<i>Through the air.</i>

00:14.743 --> 00:16.244
- Coughing--
- I'm sorry.

00:16.244 --> 00:18.204
I meant people. On planes.

00:18.204 --> 00:19.706
That was something
you described in your book.

00:19.706 --> 00:21.666
Yes, a new virus in Madagascar, say,

00:21.666 --> 00:23.793
could be in Chicago
within a matter of weeks.

00:23.793 --> 00:26.796
And we end up with a global pandemic.
Pan meaning "all."

00:26.796 --> 00:29.132
The whole world becomes sick all at once.

00:30.300 --> 00:33.136
And, Dr. Neuman,
you're also an epidemiologist.

00:33.136 --> 00:36.181
I presume the prospect of a viral pandemic
keeps you up at night as well.

00:36.181 --> 00:37.474
- No.
- No?

00:37.474 --> 00:39.100
- No.
- All right, well, that's our show.

00:40.435 --> 00:43.271
No, mankind has been at war with the virus
from the start.

00:43.271 --> 00:46.566
Sometimes, millions of people die,
as in an actual war.

00:46.566 --> 00:49.027
But in the end, we always win.

00:49.027 --> 00:52.280
But you-- just to be clear, you do think
microorganisms pose a threat.

00:52.989 --> 00:54.866
In the most dire terms.

00:54.866 --> 00:56.451
- Bacteria.
- No.

00:56.451 --> 00:58.244
- You like saying no.
- Yes.

00:59.954 --> 01:01.831
Not bacteria. Not viruses.

01:01.831 --> 01:03.792
- So?
- Fungus.

01:05.585 --> 01:07.003
Yes, that's the usual response.

01:07.462 --> 01:09.172
Fungi seem harmless enough.

01:09.172 --> 01:11.049
Many species know otherwise.

01:11.049 --> 01:14.469
Because there are some fungi
who seek not to kill,

01:14.469 --> 01:15.762
but to control.

01:15.762 --> 01:18.556
Let me ask you,
where do we get LSD from?

01:18.556 --> 01:20.475
Where do you get it from?

01:20.475 --> 01:22.769
It comes from ergot, a fungus.

01:22.769 --> 01:25.146
Psilocybin? Also a fungus.

01:25.146 --> 01:29.192
Viruses can make us ill,
but fungi can alter our very minds.

01:29.192 --> 01:31.194
There's a fungus that infects insects.

01:31.194 --> 01:32.862
Gets inside an ant, for example,

01:32.862 --> 01:36.491
travels through its circulatory system
to the ant's brain,

01:36.491 --> 01:38.535
and then floods it with hallucinogens,

01:38.535 --> 01:41.830
thus bending the ant's mind to its will.

01:41.830 --> 01:43.873
The fungus starts
to direct the ant's behavior,

01:43.873 --> 01:45.500
telling it where to go, what to do,

01:45.500 --> 01:47.794
like a puppeteer with a marionette.

01:47.794 --> 01:49.212
And it gets worse.

01:49.212 --> 01:50.797
The fungus needs food to live,

01:50.797 --> 01:54.217
so it begins to devour
its host from within,

01:54.217 --> 01:56.803
replacing the ant's flesh with its own,

01:56.803 --> 01:58.596
but it doesn't let its victim die.

01:58.596 --> 02:03.977
No, it keeps its puppet alive
by preventing decomposition.

02:03.977 --> 02:06.479
How? Where do we get penicillin from?

02:06.479 --> 02:07.397
Fungus.

02:09.190 --> 02:10.233
Dr. Schoenheiss, you're in distress.

02:10.233 --> 02:13.319
Fungal infection of this kind is real,
but not in humans.

02:13.319 --> 02:15.321
True, fungi cannot survive

02:15.321 --> 02:19.117
if its host's internal temperature
is over 94 degrees.

02:19.117 --> 02:21.786
And currently, there are no reasons
for fungi to evolve

02:21.786 --> 02:23.246
to be able to withstand
higher temperatures.

02:23.246 --> 02:24.706
But what if that were to change?

02:24.706 --> 02:27.625
What if, for instance,

02:27.625 --> 02:30.169
the world were to get slightly warmer?

02:30.628 --> 02:33.798
Well, now there is reason to evolve.

02:33.798 --> 02:38.261
One gene mutates and an ascomycete,
candida, ergot,

02:38.261 --> 02:41.264
cordyceps, aspergillus,
any one of them could become

02:41.264 --> 02:43.349
capable of burrowing into our brains

02:43.349 --> 02:47.228
and taking control not of millions of us,
but billions of us.

02:47.228 --> 02:50.565
Billions of puppets with poisoned minds

02:50.565 --> 02:53.443
permanently fixed on one unifying goal:

02:53.443 --> 02:57.906
to spread the infection
to every last human alive

02:57.906 --> 02:59.365
by any means necessary.

02:59.365 --> 03:00.742
And there are no treatments for this.

03:00.742 --> 03:03.369
No preventatives, no cures.

03:03.369 --> 03:06.289
They don't exist.
It's not even possible to make them.

03:07.749 --> 03:09.083
So, if that happens?

03:11.085 --> 03:12.629
We lose.

03:16.549 --> 03:17.800
We'll be back.

04:19.862 --> 04:24.826
THE LAST OF US

04:29.706 --> 04:33.418
2003

04:59.652 --> 05:00.903
Alarm.

05:02.238 --> 05:03.197
Alarm!

05:19.797 --> 05:22.592
- Where's the pancake mix?
- Oh, was I--

05:22.592 --> 05:24.010
Yeah, I was. Sorry.

05:24.010 --> 05:25.720
I was gonna make you birthday pancakes.

05:25.720 --> 05:27.055
I swear.

05:27.055 --> 05:28.723
You know I don't really like pancakes.

05:28.723 --> 05:31.350
I know you don't like them.
It was for my benefit.

05:35.563 --> 05:36.397
Vitamin C.

05:45.364 --> 05:47.116
You get your homework done?

05:49.368 --> 05:50.328
Fractions?

05:53.539 --> 05:54.916
How old are you again?

05:54.916 --> 05:55.792
Thirty-six.

05:56.751 --> 05:57.919
Gonna have to wear diapers soon.

05:57.919 --> 05:59.545
Who says I don't already?

06:02.965 --> 06:03.841
Shell.

06:03.841 --> 06:04.967
Calcium.

06:05.635 --> 06:06.761
Lovely.

06:08.387 --> 06:09.639
Is there enough for Uncle Tommy?

06:09.639 --> 06:11.057
Well, there would've been.

06:13.976 --> 06:15.311
You're still alive, you old fucker.

06:15.311 --> 06:17.021
Aw. He loves you.

06:17.021 --> 06:18.981
He's dependent on me. Not the same.

06:18.981 --> 06:21.150
- I think it's the same.
- It's definitely the same.

06:21.150 --> 06:22.777
I thought we was havin' pancakes.

06:23.736 --> 06:25.113
We'll pick you somethin' up on the road.

06:25.113 --> 06:27.323
- Concrete guys gonna be there?
- Yeah, they said maybe.

06:27.323 --> 06:29.075
Maybe? We can't frame until we pour.

06:29.075 --> 06:30.451
We're not gettin' paid until we frame.

06:30.451 --> 06:31.994
Well, we could bring someone else on,

06:31.994 --> 06:33.287
- get the job done faster.
- No, no.

06:33.287 --> 06:34.330
I'm not splittin' this job.

06:34.330 --> 06:35.998
I barely wanna split it with you.

06:35.998 --> 06:37.416
We could work a double.

06:37.416 --> 06:39.961
- Literally? Today?
- I know. I'd be done by nine.

06:39.961 --> 06:41.462
By nine, right?

06:42.255 --> 06:43.047
Yeah.

06:44.340 --> 06:45.591
I'll bring back a cake.

06:46.175 --> 06:47.093
I promise.

06:49.804 --> 06:52.181
<i>...continued disturbances in Jakarta,</i>

06:52.181 --> 06:53.599
<i>but are advising U.S. citizens...</i>

06:53.599 --> 06:55.768
Jakarta. Where is that, Middle East?

06:55.768 --> 06:57.770
Doesn't ring a bell.
It's definitely a country.

06:57.770 --> 07:00.064
- Or maybe part of Asia?
- Jakarta isn't a country.

07:00.064 --> 07:02.650
Being a part of Asia isn't mutually
exclusive with being a country,

07:02.650 --> 07:04.777
and in fact,
it's the capital of Indonesia.

07:05.194 --> 07:07.280
Shit. Hope for us yet.

07:14.120 --> 07:15.037
All right.

07:15.997 --> 07:17.623
Finish up quick, we'll drop you off.

07:17.623 --> 07:20.376
- I'm still eating my eggshells.
- You got seven minutes.

07:20.376 --> 07:22.128
Your t-shirt's inside out.

07:25.381 --> 07:26.716
Shit.

07:29.343 --> 07:30.261
He's losin' it.

08:12.762 --> 08:13.679
Sarah!

08:19.810 --> 08:20.978
Hey, neighbor!

08:21.729 --> 08:22.605
Oh, Hi.

08:23.231 --> 08:27.276
Connie was askin' after you,
since you haven't been over in a while.

08:27.276 --> 08:28.694
Make 'em happy.

08:29.862 --> 08:32.698
I could come by after school,
but just for, like,

08:32.698 --> 08:34.659
- a little bit?
- She'll take whatcha got.

08:34.659 --> 08:37.578
Y'all can bake, whatever.

08:37.578 --> 08:38.788
Speakin' of,

08:39.330 --> 08:40.790
we got a lotta extra here.

08:40.790 --> 08:42.500
Y'all want some biscuits?

08:43.251 --> 08:45.169
Dad, you love biscuits.

08:49.507 --> 08:50.424
I do.

08:50.883 --> 08:52.677
But I'm on Atkins.

08:52.677 --> 08:55.388
- On what now?
- It's, you know what?

08:55.388 --> 08:57.139
We gotta run, but Sarah'll be by later.

08:57.139 --> 08:58.933
She'll stay as long as you want.

08:59.600 --> 09:01.185
Tell ya all about Atkins.

09:01.185 --> 09:03.980
Great! I'll let Connie know.

09:03.980 --> 09:04.981
Solid.

09:08.442 --> 09:11.153
Can't tell you how exciting it was
listenin' to that fuckin' conversation.

09:11.153 --> 09:12.363
Put that out.

09:13.656 --> 09:15.074
Happy birthday to you.

09:15.074 --> 09:17.660
OPERATION DESERT STORM
COMBAT VETERAN

09:20.454 --> 09:25.293
AUSTIN, TX
SEPTEMBER 26th

09:25.293 --> 09:28.546
Want you to write this diagram out
exactly as I have it.

09:28.546 --> 09:29.922
Always subject and predicate.

09:29.922 --> 09:31.090
LIVE OUT LOUD
NO LIMITS

09:31.090 --> 09:32.049
Verb and noun.

09:32.049 --> 09:32.925
WE LEARN NOT IN SCHOOL, BUT IN LIFE SMILE

09:33.467 --> 09:36.137
Okay, the sentence is,
"Where are you going?" Subject is you.

09:37.096 --> 09:39.390
You are going.

09:39.390 --> 09:40.891
Predicate.

09:40.891 --> 09:42.685
Where, adverb.

09:42.685 --> 09:45.187
You see it? Okay.
Have some nods, shaking of heads.

09:45.187 --> 09:47.231
I swear you will use this later in life.

09:47.231 --> 09:49.066
Believe me, that's why you're here.

09:49.066 --> 09:50.776
Okay? So...

09:56.907 --> 09:58.451
Yes, you need to know this!

09:58.451 --> 10:00.578
Yes, it's on your test next week!

10:01.245 --> 10:04.999
Homework is due end of class tomorrow!

10:44.455 --> 10:47.792
LONE STAR
WATCH & JEWELRY

10:47.792 --> 10:49.669
LEBANON

10:59.428 --> 11:00.346
Twenty.

11:00.930 --> 11:02.098
That's it?

11:02.098 --> 11:03.391
Okay, 30.

11:04.433 --> 11:05.476
Twenty's good.

11:05.476 --> 11:08.104
It's a spring. I'll do it right now.

11:27.248 --> 11:29.417
All day. I swear.

11:32.420 --> 11:33.671
We're closing.

11:35.297 --> 11:36.590
We're done for today.

11:36.590 --> 11:38.676
It's 3:15, we close at 7.

11:41.679 --> 11:43.973
- I'm very sorry. He cannot finish.
- I'm already finished.

11:48.185 --> 11:49.728
You should go home.

11:56.110 --> 11:59.280
LONE STAR
WATCH & JEWELRY

12:08.747 --> 12:10.916
- There you are, sweetie.
- Sorry.

12:10.916 --> 12:12.376
I was gettin' worried.

12:12.376 --> 12:14.378
I was getting something for my dad.

12:15.004 --> 12:16.130
Hi, Mercy.

12:18.215 --> 12:21.802
Hey, is everything okay?
Like, on the news?

12:21.802 --> 12:23.637
Like what, hon?

12:23.637 --> 12:27.141
Well, no, there was just a lot of police
and stuff on the road today.

12:27.141 --> 12:29.059
Well, that's true every day, innit?

12:29.059 --> 12:31.479
People out there need
to get right with Jesus.

12:31.479 --> 12:35.483
Three nails, plus one cross,
equals four-given.

12:36.734 --> 12:38.694
I was thinkin' we'd make some cookies.

12:38.694 --> 12:40.029
Chocolate chip?

12:40.529 --> 12:41.655
Raisin.

12:50.247 --> 12:52.416
C'mon, Mama. It's green.

12:52.416 --> 12:53.876
You love that.

12:54.752 --> 12:56.545
Here we go!

12:56.545 --> 12:59.006
I don't know why I talk to her.

12:59.006 --> 13:01.133
She's completely deaf.

13:29.537 --> 13:30.955
You wanna give me a hand?

13:30.955 --> 13:32.164
Be right there!

13:54.395 --> 13:55.854
Hey, Mrs. Adler?

13:55.854 --> 13:57.481
Could I borrow this?

14:00.192 --> 14:01.777
Yeah, sure.

14:01.777 --> 14:03.404
It's one of Danny's.

14:04.572 --> 14:06.532
You know what?
My dad's gonna be back real soon.

14:06.532 --> 14:08.284
- I should go.
- You sure?

14:08.284 --> 14:10.911
- Yeah.
- Well, you're takin' some cookies.

14:36.145 --> 14:37.646
WELCOME

14:59.918 --> 15:02.379
<i>No comment today from
the Austin Police Department</i>

15:02.379 --> 15:05.507
<i>regarding a rash of violent incidents
across the city,</i>

15:05.507 --> 15:08.844
<i>some suggesting a new street drug
may be to blame.</i>

15:08.844 --> 15:12.222
<i>More on that when we return,
with Manuela Sanchez reporting live...</i>

15:19.813 --> 15:21.774
You locked the door for once.

15:21.774 --> 15:22.775
Good job.

15:23.484 --> 15:24.360
Yeah.

15:29.448 --> 15:31.283
- It's 10.
- I know.

15:31.283 --> 15:34.912
They gave us the wrong size
for the headers.

15:35.663 --> 15:38.499
That doesn't mean anything to ya.
I'm sorry.

15:38.499 --> 15:39.917
Where's the cake?

15:40.584 --> 15:42.419
- Shit.
- C'mon, man.

15:42.419 --> 15:44.004
I'll get us one tomorrow.

15:44.004 --> 15:47.174
Swear, or you don't get your present.

15:47.174 --> 15:49.927
- You got me a present?
- Swear.

15:49.927 --> 15:51.136
On my life.

15:58.811 --> 15:59.937
Wow.

16:03.941 --> 16:05.484
Fixed it for you.

16:12.616 --> 16:13.909
- Did you?
- What?

16:13.909 --> 16:15.119
I don't hear anything.

16:16.537 --> 16:17.705
That was lame.

16:17.705 --> 16:19.915
- You're lame.
- Yeah, I know.

16:20.999 --> 16:22.876
Where'd you get the money for this?

16:22.876 --> 16:24.753
Drugs. I sell hardcore drugs.

16:24.753 --> 16:26.004
It's better than what I do.

16:26.004 --> 16:29.007
It was only $20, which I stole from you.

16:29.883 --> 16:32.052
I could've stolen 60,
but I put the change back

16:32.052 --> 16:33.721
because I'm an honest thief.

16:33.721 --> 16:35.556
Besides, it's the thought that counts.

16:35.556 --> 16:37.850
And you were never gonna
do it for yourself, so.

16:42.938 --> 16:44.064
Thank you.

16:46.984 --> 16:47.901
There's one more.

16:50.988 --> 16:53.115
- Borrowed it from the Adlers.
- This is the one with the deleted scenes.

16:53.115 --> 16:54.158
"ONE OF THE BEST PERFORMANCES
I'VE EVER SEEN"

16:54.158 --> 16:56.368
Yeah, imagine how bad those have to be.

16:56.368 --> 16:58.996
C'mon, pop it in.
While it's still your birthday.

17:08.297 --> 17:10.007
- Don't fall asleep.
-'Course, I won't.

17:10.007 --> 17:11.717
It's too riveting.

17:33.864 --> 17:34.823
Hello?

17:34.823 --> 17:36.241
<i>Joel, it's me.</i>

17:37.034 --> 17:37.951
<i>I'm okay.</i>

17:38.494 --> 17:40.621
- Yeah?
-<i>But I'm in jail.</i>

17:41.580 --> 17:43.832
- Goddammit.
-<i>Wasn't my fault this time.</i>

17:43.832 --> 17:46.794
<i>I was at the bar, some guy goes crazy,
starts swingin' at a waitress,</i>

17:46.794 --> 17:48.587
<i>I stepped in, knocked him out,
cops show up--</i>

17:48.587 --> 17:50.005
<i>Look, it doesn't fuckin' matter.</i>

17:50.005 --> 17:51.548
-<i>You gotta bail me out.</i>
- Now?

17:51.548 --> 17:54.551
<i>It's Friday, you don't get me out tonight,
I'm in here all weekend.</i>

17:54.551 --> 17:56.345
<i>It's a fuckin' madhouse, Joel.</i>

17:56.345 --> 17:58.847
-<i>I gotta get out.</i>
- Well, which jail? Travis County?

17:58.847 --> 18:00.265
<i>Yeah, on 10th.</i>

18:00.265 --> 18:02.893
- Goddammit, Tommy.
-<i>I'm sorry.</i>

18:04.812 --> 18:05.646
<i>Please.</i>

18:07.314 --> 18:08.106
Okay.

18:08.607 --> 18:10.359
Fuckin' idiot.

18:32.256 --> 18:35.384
11:03 PM

19:12.629 --> 19:13.755
Dad?

19:22.973 --> 19:24.099
Dad?!

19:41.867 --> 19:42.951
<i>...indoors.
Law enforcement and emergency services</i>

19:42.951 --> 19:44.244
NATIONAL ALERT PRIMARY ENTRY POINT SYSTEM
ISSUED AN EMERGENCY ACTION NOTIFICATION

19:44.244 --> 19:47.998
<i>are in the area and will be in contact
with further instructions.</i>

19:50.751 --> 19:52.711
<i>Stay indoors, law enforcement...</i>

19:59.468 --> 20:01.762
Easy. Easy, Mercy.

20:02.804 --> 20:04.681
What're you doing out here, boy?

20:32.459 --> 20:34.378
C'mon, let's get you home.

20:38.131 --> 20:40.175
C'mon, Mercy. Please.

20:40.175 --> 20:41.385
Mercy!

20:52.437 --> 20:54.064
Mrs. Adler?

21:14.376 --> 21:15.711
Mrs. Adler?

21:45.407 --> 21:46.950
Mrs. Adler?

22:01.131 --> 22:02.674
Help me.

22:53.058 --> 22:55.018
Get in the truck! Right now!

22:55.560 --> 22:57.312
Move!

23:08.365 --> 23:09.449
What are we doin', Joel?

23:25.841 --> 23:28.135
- You killed her.
- Baby, I'm sorry.

23:28.135 --> 23:30.053
- Joel, we gotta go.
- Sarah, listen to me.

23:30.053 --> 23:31.763
It's not just the Adlers.

23:31.763 --> 23:34.349
But we're gonna be brave,
and we're gonna get outta this.

23:35.350 --> 23:37.144
Hey. Let's go. Come on.

23:37.936 --> 23:39.062
Get in.

23:40.772 --> 23:42.190
Joel?

23:42.190 --> 23:44.025
Denise, you get back inside the house!

23:44.025 --> 23:47.237
- You lock your doors! Now!
- C'mon, c'mon, get in!

23:56.329 --> 23:57.831
- Get your seat belt on.
- Hold on.

24:01.877 --> 24:03.753
Jesus Christ, Joel!

24:07.799 --> 24:09.885
- You take 70--
- 71, I know.

24:10.260 --> 24:11.553
AUSTIN
SAN MARCOS

24:11.553 --> 24:13.013
HOSPITAL

24:18.894 --> 24:19.853
- Daddy--
- We don't know.

24:19.853 --> 24:22.439
They're saying it's a virus.
Some kind of parasite.

24:22.439 --> 24:24.065
Is it from terrorists?

24:24.065 --> 24:26.359
We don't know.

24:26.818 --> 24:28.862
- Are we sick?
- No. Of course not.

24:28.862 --> 24:30.322
Why did things blow up?

24:30.322 --> 24:32.616
No cellphone, no radio.

24:32.616 --> 24:34.034
Minute ago, newsman wouldn't shut up.

24:34.034 --> 24:36.036
- How do you know?
- What?

24:36.036 --> 24:38.288
How do you know we're not sick?

24:38.288 --> 24:40.916
They're saying it's mostly
people in the city.

24:40.916 --> 24:42.918
That's why they got
the highway blocked off.

24:46.463 --> 24:47.380
God.

24:47.964 --> 24:49.716
It's Jimmy's place.

24:58.850 --> 25:01.228
The Adlers would take Nana into the city.

25:01.228 --> 25:02.896
To the hospital for stuff.

25:02.896 --> 25:05.899
That's right. They would.
That's probably why.

25:08.401 --> 25:12.197
But, you'd have to go a lot, right?

25:12.197 --> 25:13.615
We're fine. Trust me.

25:17.535 --> 25:19.079
All right.

25:24.209 --> 25:25.794
Here! Right here!

25:25.794 --> 25:27.545
- Hey!
- What are you doin'?

25:27.545 --> 25:30.215
- Got a kid, Joel.
- So do we. Keep driving.

25:30.215 --> 25:32.801
We could put them in the back.

25:35.679 --> 25:37.597
Somebody else'll come along.

25:48.149 --> 25:50.443
Fuck! Everybody had the same fuckin' idea.

25:51.903 --> 25:52.779
I can't get through this.

