So, you march outta here
all Clint Eastwood,

53:59.172 --> 54:01.007
he's gonna get wind of it and skip.

54:01.007 --> 54:03.301
I need you to take a breath.

54:09.099 --> 54:10.809
- Who'd he sell it to?
- Don't know.

54:10.809 --> 54:13.061
- Well, where is he?
- Don't know.

54:13.812 --> 54:14.688
Yet.

54:15.647 --> 54:18.400
But we're gonna find out, quietly.

54:18.858 --> 54:20.151
Understand?

54:21.611 --> 54:23.697
Now I promised Robert
that you wouldn't hurt him.

54:25.031 --> 54:28.159
But I would very much
like for you to hurt him.

54:28.159 --> 54:31.204
So let's go hunt that motherfucker down,

54:31.204 --> 54:33.915
and get our battery and our truck,

54:33.915 --> 54:35.917
and then we'll go find Tommy.

54:36.376 --> 54:37.168
All right?

54:40.338 --> 54:41.256
All right.

55:05.030 --> 55:06.531
The team in place at Southeast 3?

55:08.199 --> 55:09.284
I held them back.

55:10.493 --> 55:12.203
I have some questions.

55:12.912 --> 55:13.705
Okay.

55:15.290 --> 55:17.333
We've been blowing up
meaningless FEDRA targets

55:17.333 --> 55:19.711
spread out all over the QZ, for two weeks.

55:19.711 --> 55:21.755
We've already lost four people,
and we're--

55:23.006 --> 55:24.007
What's the point of this?

55:25.675 --> 55:27.343
Is that your question?

55:27.343 --> 55:29.095
That's one of them.

55:29.095 --> 55:30.597
My answer is to follow fuckin' orders.

55:31.473 --> 55:33.349
And why do you have some random girl
locked in a room?

55:33.349 --> 55:36.144
And the guys you have guarding her
won't tell me shit?

55:36.144 --> 55:39.773
Our people are asking what's going on,
and I don't know what to tell them.

55:39.773 --> 55:42.150
Tell them to follow fuckin' orders.

55:42.150 --> 55:44.360
You two, go to Southeast 3. Now.

55:50.617 --> 55:52.452
- Kim.
- Marlene.

55:52.452 --> 55:55.121
We are in a war
against a military dictatorship

55:55.121 --> 55:56.998
to restore democracy and freedom.

55:56.998 --> 55:57.999
Does that sound about right?

55:57.999 --> 55:59.084
- Yes?
- Are we winning?

55:59.084 --> 56:00.293
Are we beating FEDRA here?

56:00.293 --> 56:01.878
Are the Fireflies beating FEDRA anywhere?

56:01.878 --> 56:04.047
- Rebellion takes time.
- You fight for 20 years

56:04.047 --> 56:05.507
and you get nowhere,
you're not a rebellion.

56:06.049 --> 56:07.759
Just spray paint.

56:08.843 --> 56:11.304
We're not hitting FEDRA "all over" the QZ.

56:11.304 --> 56:14.891
We hit 'em here, here, here, here, here.

56:15.809 --> 56:16.810
Where are we right now?

56:18.895 --> 56:21.272
I want FEDRA everywhere but here.

56:21.272 --> 56:24.025
I want them as distracted as possible
because tonight,

56:24.025 --> 56:26.528
every Firefly in Boston
is gonna gather in this building,

56:26.528 --> 56:28.780
and we are gonna leave the QZ. Permanently.

56:30.115 --> 56:31.783
- We're quitting?
- No.

56:31.783 --> 56:34.869
We're taking that random girl
locked in that room west.

56:36.871 --> 56:38.957
From our guy in the radio tower in Salem.

56:47.757 --> 56:49.050
Is this real?

56:49.926 --> 56:51.469
I believe it is.

56:54.973 --> 56:56.141
Keep it quiet.

56:59.435 --> 57:01.229
Whatever you need.

57:01.229 --> 57:02.689
Whatever it takes.

57:02.689 --> 57:04.691
We'll get her where she needs to go.

57:34.095 --> 57:34.929
Hey, friend.

57:36.931 --> 57:38.349
Don't worry. I don't want anything.

57:39.142 --> 57:40.727
But if you're feelin' lost--

57:40.727 --> 57:43.354
You tell me to "look for the light"
and I'll break your jaw.

57:54.032 --> 57:57.577
Well, it cost us a couple of cards,
but we got him.

57:58.119 --> 58:01.289
He's supposedly takin' the battery
to a red-tagged building.

58:01.289 --> 58:04.500
But get this,
corner of Stillman and Cross.

58:04.500 --> 58:06.252
The one Miguel used to use.

58:06.252 --> 58:08.004
Yeah, I'm thinkin' so.

58:08.004 --> 58:10.089
We can take the subway tunnel
under Haymarket,

58:10.089 --> 58:13.218
get into the building from below,
and take Robert by surprise.

58:13.843 --> 58:15.136
Pay this fucker back.

58:23.561 --> 58:24.437
Oh, my God.

58:30.026 --> 58:31.861
Agh! You fucker!

58:38.201 --> 58:40.745
One, two, three, four--

59:08.856 --> 59:09.941
You're not scared.

59:13.152 --> 59:14.862
Then unlock me.

59:14.862 --> 59:16.489
How about we start with "thank you"?

59:16.489 --> 59:17.824
For what?

59:17.824 --> 59:19.575
For saving your life?

59:19.575 --> 59:21.077
I am the one who told 'em
not to shoot you,

59:21.077 --> 59:23.079
- if you recall.
- Yeah.

59:30.461 --> 59:31.462
Why did you stop them?

59:32.797 --> 59:33.923
We'll get to that.

59:48.146 --> 59:50.315
So, Veronica,

59:52.734 --> 59:54.068
how ya feelin'?

59:55.820 --> 59:56.946
The same.

59:59.032 --> 1:00:00.575
Is it gonna happen?

1:00:02.827 --> 1:00:03.745
No.

1:00:07.123 --> 1:00:08.124
So, can I go?

1:00:09.250 --> 1:00:10.251
No.

1:00:10.251 --> 1:00:12.128
I won't tell anyone about any of this.

1:00:12.128 --> 1:00:13.338
I swear.

1:00:13.338 --> 1:00:14.505
Where you gonna go?

1:00:14.505 --> 1:00:16.257
Back to FEDRA military school?

1:00:16.257 --> 1:00:19.469
- You that anxious to be a soldier?
- You think I chose that place?

1:00:19.469 --> 1:00:21.304
They put me there when I was a baby.

1:00:21.304 --> 1:00:22.597
It's for orphans.

1:00:22.597 --> 1:00:24.474
"They" didn't put you there.

1:00:26.434 --> 1:00:27.560
I did.

1:00:28.394 --> 1:00:29.520
Ellie.

1:00:33.358 --> 1:00:34.859
You my fucking mom or something?

1:00:35.568 --> 1:00:37.445
Do I look like your mom?

1:00:38.071 --> 1:00:40.198
Nooo, you do not.

1:00:41.240 --> 1:00:42.909
My name is Marlene.

1:00:42.909 --> 1:00:45.453
I'm the leader of the Fireflies
in the Boston QZ.

1:00:46.704 --> 1:00:48.498
Why would a terrorist dump me with FEDRA?

1:00:48.498 --> 1:00:50.666
Because it's where you'd be safest,
and you were safe there

1:00:50.666 --> 1:00:51.918
until you decided to sneak out.

1:00:51.918 --> 1:00:53.544
And "terrorist"?

1:00:54.379 --> 1:00:55.713
Was Riley a terrorist?

1:01:12.480 --> 1:01:14.565
Why won't you let me go home?

1:01:18.236 --> 1:01:21.406
Because you have a greater purpose
than any of us could've ever imagined.

1:01:22.657 --> 1:01:26.077
So we're leaving tonight,
and we're taking you with us.

1:01:28.788 --> 1:01:30.915
- He's here.
- Five minutes.

1:01:35.378 --> 1:01:37.797
What I'm about to tell you
cannot be repeated to anyone.

1:01:38.589 --> 1:01:41.759
Because if you do, I assure you

1:01:43.428 --> 1:01:44.971
you will die.

1:01:47.723 --> 1:01:50.268
HAYMARKET ACCESS 838

1:02:07.368 --> 1:02:08.369
Okay.

1:02:09.454 --> 1:02:10.371
Ready?

1:02:10.872 --> 1:02:11.789
Yeah.

1:02:29.348 --> 1:02:30.516
That's the one.

1:02:55.374 --> 1:02:56.626
Oh fuck.

1:02:56.626 --> 1:02:57.919
Oh shit.

1:02:59.962 --> 1:03:01.088
This one's done.

1:03:03.591 --> 1:03:04.509
Yeah.

1:03:05.343 --> 1:03:06.511
I know. I just--

1:03:06.511 --> 1:03:08.095
I wasn't expecting it.

1:03:08.095 --> 1:03:09.805
Take it he wasn't down here last time?

1:03:11.015 --> 1:03:11.933
No.

1:03:14.602 --> 1:03:16.395
You think he came down
after he was infected?

1:03:18.648 --> 1:03:21.234
Well, maybe down here
is where he was infected.

1:03:25.863 --> 1:03:27.406
Let's keep movin'.

1:03:41.546 --> 1:03:43.965
It's like they reframed
the whole structure.

1:03:43.965 --> 1:03:45.466
Probably in the '80s.

1:03:45.466 --> 1:03:47.343
Everyone was cutting down
on apartment sizes

1:03:47.343 --> 1:03:48.511
to sell more condos.

1:03:49.303 --> 1:03:53.891
"This has been 'Construction Corner'
with Joel Miller."

1:03:53.891 --> 1:03:55.184
How far up we goin'?

1:03:57.853 --> 1:03:59.021
This far.

1:04:01.857 --> 1:04:05.778
So, this opens into the hallway.

1:04:06.696 --> 1:04:09.615
What the fuck?
Someone put a piano in front of this?

1:04:12.660 --> 1:04:13.995
You smell that?

1:04:15.871 --> 1:04:17.999
Yeah, gunpowder.

1:04:24.547 --> 1:04:25.840
Tess.

1:04:46.777 --> 1:04:48.195
Well, the battery's no good.

1:04:49.071 --> 1:04:50.990
And he still tried to sell it.

1:04:51.824 --> 1:04:52.950
Twice.

1:04:53.993 --> 1:04:55.620
You greedy fuck.

1:05:09.759 --> 1:05:10.885
Shit.

1:05:10.885 --> 1:05:12.470
Oh God.

1:05:15.431 --> 1:05:17.058
Shit, come on.

1:05:24.190 --> 1:05:25.274
Fuck.

1:05:27.902 --> 1:05:28.986
Joel?

1:05:30.196 --> 1:05:31.155
Marlene?

1:05:33.366 --> 1:05:35.284
- You okay?
- Yeah.

1:05:37.828 --> 1:05:39.246
Ellie.

1:05:39.246 --> 1:05:40.456
Ellie!

1:05:42.792 --> 1:05:45.628
- Oh shit!
- No, it's okay. I'll be all right.

1:05:45.628 --> 1:05:47.672
And you can't be stupid like this.

1:05:49.173 --> 1:05:51.676
So this is who Robert
screwed us over with?

1:05:51.676 --> 1:05:53.636
The Che Guevara of Boston?

1:05:53.636 --> 1:05:55.137
War must be goin' pretty shitty

1:05:55.137 --> 1:05:57.014
for you to be buying
from scumbags like him.

1:05:57.014 --> 1:05:58.265
Yeah, it kinda has been.

1:05:58.265 --> 1:05:59.809
The merch was bad,

1:05:59.809 --> 1:06:01.560
and he obviously didn't take "fuck off"
for an answer.

1:06:01.560 --> 1:06:03.604
- Gimme my knife.
- What do you need a car battery for?

1:06:04.647 --> 1:06:06.190
- Don't.
- Not at her.

1:06:08.192 --> 1:06:09.527
Point it at me.

1:06:22.456 --> 1:06:25.126
And to answer your question,
I need it for a better reason than you do.

1:06:25.126 --> 1:06:27.002
No offense, but Tommy's just one man.

1:06:28.212 --> 1:06:31.173
- It's our business to know things.
-"To know things."

1:06:31.173 --> 1:06:33.509
You're the cause of it.
You turned my own brother against me.

1:06:33.509 --> 1:06:35.052
- Okay, Joel.
- That was a lot of gunfire.

1:06:35.052 --> 1:06:37.096
- FEDRA's gonna be on the way.
- I know.

1:06:42.268 --> 1:06:44.437
We were gonna move Ellie
outta the zone tonight.

1:06:44.437 --> 1:06:47.481
But we won't make it anywhere like this.
Not for a while anyway.

1:06:47.481 --> 1:06:50.901
So now I'm thinkin', you're gonna do it.

1:06:50.901 --> 1:06:51.986
- The hell we are.
- I'm not goin' with them!

1:06:51.986 --> 1:06:54.196
- Let me take her.
- Tess, we don't have time for this.

1:06:54.196 --> 1:06:55.406
You don't have time?

1:06:55.406 --> 1:06:56.657
- Who is she?
- To you? She's cargo.

1:06:56.657 --> 1:06:58.159
We don't smuggle people. Sorry.

1:06:58.159 --> 1:06:59.452
- I can do it.
- Kim, you don't have

1:06:59.452 --> 1:07:00.953
a fuckin' ear on your fuckin' head.

1:07:00.953 --> 1:07:01.829
Could you please?

1:07:03.414 --> 1:07:06.250
There's a team of Fireflies
waiting for her at the old State House.

1:07:06.250 --> 1:07:08.043
I know what's out there.

1:07:08.043 --> 1:07:11.130
We were going with an entire squadron
for that very reason.

1:07:11.130 --> 1:07:12.882
But now I don't have a truck,
I don't have a squadron,

1:07:12.882 --> 1:07:14.216
FEDRA's five minutes away.

1:07:14.216 --> 1:07:16.218
What I do have is you.

1:07:16.218 --> 1:07:18.929
And I know what you're both capable of.

1:07:18.929 --> 1:07:20.431
For better or worse.

1:07:23.350 --> 1:07:24.935
What are they capable of?

1:07:24.935 --> 1:07:27.772
You get her there safely,
and they'll give you what you need.

1:07:27.772 --> 1:07:29.732
Not just a battery. The whole thing.

1:07:29.732 --> 1:07:32.485
Fueled-up truck, guns,
supplies, all of it.

1:07:32.485 --> 1:07:33.819
I swear.

1:07:36.655 --> 1:07:37.990
I swear.

1:07:45.748 --> 1:07:46.791
Asshole!

1:07:52.838 --> 1:07:54.423
You trust her?

1:07:54.423 --> 1:07:56.425
No, me neither, but she seems desperate.

1:07:56.425 --> 1:07:59.094
Firefly vehicle usually means
repurposed FEDRA stuff.

1:07:59.094 --> 1:08:01.555
So better-than-decent chance
makin' it to Tommy in one of those.

1:08:01.555 --> 1:08:03.140
The second we hand that kid over--

1:08:03.140 --> 1:08:06.143
Y'all talk it through,
but please remember that I'm bleeding out.

1:08:10.231 --> 1:08:11.649
Okay. Here's the deal.

1:08:12.608 --> 1:08:14.568
We'll get her to your crew
at the State House.

1:08:14.568 --> 1:08:18.030
But before we hand her over,
they give us everything that we want.

1:08:18.030 --> 1:08:19.990
If not, we kill her, there and then.

1:08:19.990 --> 1:08:22.117
- Deal.
- Really? That fast?

1:08:22.117 --> 1:08:23.869
You are all that matters.

1:08:23.869 --> 1:08:25.746
My team will not jeopardize that.

1:08:25.746 --> 1:08:27.373
Remember what I told you?

1:08:27.373 --> 1:08:28.374
Now go get your backpack.

1:08:30.042 --> 1:08:31.460
Now, Ellie.

1:08:41.929 --> 1:08:43.055
Let's go.

1:08:51.021 --> 1:08:52.356
Joel,

1:08:54.358 --> 1:08:55.901
don't fuck this up.

1:08:58.237 --> 1:08:59.363
Please.

1:09:50.623 --> 1:09:52.208
Give us a minute, all right?

1:09:52.208 --> 1:09:53.375
What the fuck?!

1:09:55.127 --> 1:09:56.670
So, what's the plan?

1:09:57.922 --> 1:09:59.381
There's not a lot of options.

1:09:59.840 --> 1:10:02.092
There's the short way or the long way.

1:10:02.092 --> 1:10:03.761
The short way is pretty much...

1:10:03.761 --> 1:10:05.346
That leaves the long way.

1:10:05.346 --> 1:10:07.348
Things look bad,
we'll come up with something.

1:10:07.348 --> 1:10:08.307
We'll have to drop,
head to Bill and Frank's.

1:10:08.307 --> 1:10:09.308
ROAD ATLAS

1:10:09.934 --> 1:10:12.269
Stock up on anything we may need.

1:10:17.858 --> 1:10:19.526
THE BILLBOARD BOOK
OF NUMBER 1 HITS

1:10:27.952 --> 1:10:31.038
We leave after dark. Stay with the kid.

1:10:32.206 --> 1:10:33.332
Wait. Why do I have to-- Tess.

1:10:33.332 --> 1:10:34.875
B/F

1:10:34.875 --> 1:10:36.335
60 - NOTHING IN

1:10:36.335 --> 1:10:37.670
70 - NEW STOCK

1:10:37.670 --> 1:10:38.963
80 - X

1:10:44.259 --> 1:10:45.427
So, who's Bill and Frank?

1:10:49.098 --> 1:10:51.100
The radio's a smuggling code, right?

1:10:51.100 --> 1:10:52.810
'60s song, they don't have anything new,

1:10:52.810 --> 1:10:54.228
'70s, they got new stuff.

1:10:54.228 --> 1:10:55.562
What's '80s?

1:11:02.528 --> 1:11:03.821
What are you doing?

1:11:03.821 --> 1:11:05.781
- Killin' time.
- Well, what am I supposed to do?

1:11:05.781 --> 1:11:07.408
I'm sure you'll figure that out.

1:11:15.249 --> 1:11:16.792
Your watch is broken.

1:11:31.974 --> 1:11:33.600
You mumble in your sleep.

1:11:41.608 --> 1:11:44.111
I've never been on the other side
of the Wall.

1:11:45.154 --> 1:11:46.572
Look how dark it is.

1:11:53.704 --> 1:11:55.247
You guys go out there a lot?

1:11:56.457 --> 1:11:58.459
- I guess.
- When was the last time?

1:11:58.459 --> 1:12:00.169
Maybe a year. What's it matter?

1:12:00.169 --> 1:12:01.795
But you know where to go.

1:12:03.088 --> 1:12:04.631
So we're gonna be okay.

1:12:09.386 --> 1:12:10.304
Yeah.

1:12:17.686 --> 1:12:19.063
So what's the deal with you anyway?

1:12:19.063 --> 1:12:20.981
You some kinda
bigwig's daughter or somethin'?

1:12:23.275 --> 1:12:24.818
Something like that.

1:12:34.286 --> 1:12:35.788
The radio came on when you were sleeping.

1:12:36.413 --> 1:12:37.706
What?

1:12:37.706 --> 1:12:38.749
What was the song?

1:12:38.749 --> 1:12:39.875
He kept sayin', like,

1:12:39.875 --> 1:12:42.544
"Wake me up before you go-go"?

1:12:43.545 --> 1:12:44.546
Shit.

1:12:45.923 --> 1:12:46.715
Gotcha.

1:12:47.382 --> 1:12:49.510
'80s means trouble.

1:12:50.344 --> 1:12:52.096
Code broken.

1:12:54.932 --> 1:12:56.100
Listen--

1:13:01.814 --> 1:13:04.400
The spot under Lancaster looks good.

1:13:04.400 --> 1:13:06.360
- You got a jacket in your pack?
- Yeah.

1:13:06.360 --> 1:13:08.612
Okay, get it. It's time to go.

1:13:20.874 --> 1:13:25.087
<i>...mandatory curfew
to fight infection and insurrection.</i>

1:13:28.090 --> 1:13:30.050
<i>Observe mandatory curfew</i>

1:13:30.050 --> 1:13:33.262
<i>to fight infection and insurrection.</i>

1:13:33.262 --> 1:13:36.306
WELCOME

1:14:21.977 --> 1:14:24.646
Holy shit. I'm actually outside.

1:14:24.646 --> 1:14:25.981
- Jesus Christ.
- Shit.

1:14:29.318 --> 1:14:32.905
Okay, we're gonna take the left edge
around the buffer zone.

1:14:32.905 --> 1:14:35.324
You stay close and you follow my lead.

1:14:35.824 --> 1:14:36.825
Yeah. Yeah, of course.

1:14:38.410 --> 1:14:39.536
Let's go.

1:16:10.669 --> 1:16:11.837
What the hell?

1:16:11.837 --> 1:16:13.297
Hey, hey! Don't, don't, don't move.

1:16:15.215 --> 1:16:16.049
Don't move!

1:16:22.431 --> 1:16:23.473
You gotta be shittin' me.

1:16:24.182 --> 1:16:26.143
- Okay, let's talk this out.
- Turn around.

1:16:26.143 --> 1:16:27.227
- Hold on--
- Get on your fuckin' knees.

1:16:27.227 --> 1:16:28.395
Get on your fuckin' knees!

1:16:28.395 --> 1:16:29.980
- Now hold on--
- What did I fuckin' tell you, man?

1:16:29.980 --> 1:16:31.732
I said stay the fuck home.

1:16:31.732 --> 1:16:33.567
Get on your knees!

1:16:33.567 --> 1:16:35.444
Just get on your knees,
just get on your knees.

1:16:35.444 --> 1:16:38.238
Listen, you let us do this run,

1:16:38.238 --> 1:16:39.781
we'll split the cards with you.

1:16:39.781 --> 1:16:41.074
- Will you?
- Yeah.

1:16:41.074 --> 1:16:42.159
I'm so blessed.

1:16:42.159 --> 1:16:43.869
Hands on your head. Eyes forward.

1:16:44.619 --> 1:16:45.829
Hands on your head!

1:16:49.458 --> 1:16:51.877
- Really, man?
- Yep. We're doin' this by the book.

1:16:53.128 --> 1:16:54.713
Jesus Christ.

1:16:54.713 --> 1:16:56.298
All right. What about three-quarters?

1:16:57.549 --> 1:16:59.092
Unauthorized exit.

1:16:59.092 --> 1:17:00.177
They'll hang you for that.

